==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stilbite
<hw>Stil"bite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to glitter,
shine: cf. F. <ets>stilbite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
common mineral of the zeolite family, a hydrous silicate of alumina and
lime, usually occurring in sheaflike aggregations of crystals, also in
radiated masses. It is of a white or yellowish color, with pearly luster
on the cleavage surface. Called also
<altname>desmine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

